reviews.review: Exciting and fitting conclusion to the series...!

Despite obvious lack of plan by Disney about the new trilogy, the last movie in it is quite entertaining for the reason Revenge of the Sith is... It is extremely fun without nitpicking it to death. It has some MAJOR pacing, plot, fan service issues, but the major arc of the franchise between Kylo Ren and Rey reaches a satisfying conclusion (with one small exception) in a pretty great final act...which is fun, but obviously as a Star Wars fan there was a lot to be desired in terms of storytelling logic and consistency.

One of the best Stars Wars ever!   As a young boy I saw the original in the theater in 1977 and feel episode 9 tied up the last trilogy very well and tugs at your emotions and nostalgia.  My 16-yr son thought it was the best movie he’s ever seen!   Anyone that doesn’t like this film doesn’t get the original vision of Lucas.
Fantastic story, great action, and good comedy.

While not a perfect movie, J.J. Abrams did a wonderful job of straightening out Rian Johnson's many many mistakes in The Last Jedi. What could have been had he not had to do that? This movie was so much fun and wonderfully paid service to fans. There were moments I laughed and a few where I couldn't help but cry (here's looking at you Chewie). I loved this movie and cannot wait to see it again.
Great way to close the 9 movie saga...
My 25 yr old daughter and son-in-law said it was a dumpster fire. They were so excited to go and hated it.
I liked how it brought closure to the stories but allowed for a new beginning.  It was wonderful
Anyone who is a Star Wars fan needs to see this movie

IF you spent years following Star Wars, reading the books, seeing the TV shows, watching the movies over and over, learning the lore and intricacies of this universe... you wont be impressed, you will be disgusted by what you see. Plot hole after plot hole being opened and exploited.

If you saw Star wars once as a kid and know nothing of the universe, you will be in awe of the CGI and you may even think the story is cool, but for a movie made for the fans, its shit
